    - Temperature typically reduces stiffness, so an exponential decay term with temperature can model this effect.
    - Nonlinear strain effects are captured by polynomial terms.
    - Interaction terms between strain and temperature capture coupling effects.
    - Include an exponential decay term to represent stiffness reduction with increasing temperature.

