    - Add a logarithmic temperature term to model softening/stiffening effects that saturate at high temperatures.
    - Add a strain-dependent exponential term modulated by temperature squared to capture complex thermal-mechanical coupling.
    - Include a reciprocal strain squared term to capture possible singular behavior near zero strain.
    
